Overview

  • Stacking Systems: PS3 [Liberation Maiden SIN] and PSV [Kaihou Shoujo SIN]
  • Estimated trophy difficulty: 2/10
  • Offline: 44 (1 4 7 32 )
  • Online: N/A
  • Approximate time: 6 - 8 Hours ( 3 - 5 Hours on Vita)
  • Does Difficulty affect Trophies: N/A
  • Does Difficulty levels stack: N/A
  • Missable trophies: None if you follow the guide
  • Extra Items for the Game: None
  • Glitched trophies: None
  • Cheats: None

Where to buy

PS3


PSV

 
 
 
Controls
 
- Action Button
- Cancel Button
- Menu
- Autoskip
- Activate scenes during game


 OPTIONS SETUP






TRIANGLE EVENTS
 
When the game stops on the triangle events, press to activate words on the screen.  If you setup with the options above, it will automatically stop on these for you.
 
I will not mention this in the guide since it is obvious.
 
As a side note, once you get a event it is collected forever.  So in the future, you will just pass over it.  Also, you have to play through the game two times so if you think you accidentally skipped over 1 or 2 you can collect them later on.
 
 
SAVING GAME
 
When you reach an ending, a screen will popup asking you to save.  When you reach this, press the left option twice to save the game.
